<p><a name="fall_2013_van_der_hoek_co-edits_book_on_software_designers"></a><b>van der Hoek co-edits book on software designers</b></p>
<div class="img_caption_left"><img alt="photo: Andr&#233; van der Hoek" height="90" src="../../../bin/img/photos/faculty/avanderh.jpg" width="70"/>
<p><b> Andr&#233; <br/> van der Hoek </b></p>
</div>
<p>
Professor <b>Andr&#233; van der Hoek</b>, chair of the Department of Informatics and head of the 
<a href="http://sdcl.ics.uci.edu/">Software Design and Collaboration Laboratory</a>
at UCI, has co-edited a new book released Sept. 10. 
<a href="http://www.amazon.com/Software-Designers-Action-Human-Centric-Innovations/dp/146650109X/ref=sr_1_2?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1378993404&amp;sr=8-2&amp;keywords=software+designers+in+action">Software Designers in Action: A Human-Centric Look at Design Work</a>, 
part of the Chapman &amp; Hall/CRC Innovations in Software Engineering and Software Development Series, takes a look at how developers design their software. Co-edited by 
<a href="http://mcs.open.ac.uk/mp8/">Marian Petre</a>, 
the book features an interdisciplinary selection of writings that provide a comprehensive exploration of early software design, as well as an examination of how human interaction influences software design.
</p>
</div>
<p>&#160;</p>
